{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4e1afc92-482d-4e15-92a1-3e4d5f84a6ff","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules defined in files listed **before** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Domain.fs` is listed after it.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_fr74NKhU8w5SgGHrJ6YY1B","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-6a672cc645574b12bd07205c75d4c4fd/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-6a672cc645574b12bd07205c75d4c4fd/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"36daf863-28c3-4a54-b81b-de7787d2adab","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed before them in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n```xml\n<Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n```\n\n`Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` is listed after `Services.fs`. The correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` (defines types)\n2. `Services.fs` (uses Domain types)\n\n\n3. `Program.fs` (uses both)","outputTokens":445,"requestId":"7C10:B0316:ABA19C:C4368A:6A02799E"},"id":"76703c54-7688-4d5c-b2fc-16e98fd76e32","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:51:49.297Z","parentId":"4c8e9851-cfd7-4842-bb9d-55418fd521e1"}
